-- Pick n Pay Expects `Single Digit' Growth in First Half of Year, CEO Says
-- Mike Cohen
-- 2010-06-18T09:29:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/pick-n-pay-expects-single-digit-growth-in-first-half-of-year-ceo-says.html

          
          
             Pick N Pay’s sales in the first
three months of its financial year were “flat” and it expects
“single digit” growth in the first half of the year.  
 The company sold 110,000 shirts for the soccer World Cup,
Nick Badminton, the company’s chief executive officer, said in
Cape Town today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
